    - target: {fileID: 1654144064168446860, guid: 427b27878d394274b9b107833f21bcfd, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_text
      value: 'Players begin each level with three lives.


        Incorrectly petrifying
        an innocent subject will cause the player to lose a life, but the stage will
        continue rather than immediately restarting. This allows players to recover
        from mistakes and continue investigating remaining subjects.


        Once
        all three lives are lost, the level resets and the investigation must begin
        again.'
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
